item.title: Big UK, Japan fears over China’s HK laws
item.description: Japan is seriously concerned about the move by China's parliament to go forward with national security legislation for Hong Kong which observers fear might endanger its special autonomy and freedoms.

item.title: Attenborough to set out vision for future
item.description: Sir David Attenborough has warned of imminent danger to the natural world as he prepares to set out his vision for the future in a new book.

item.title: Hundreds flee Zimbabwe, Malawi quarantines
item.description: Manhunts have begun for hundreds of people, some with coronavirus, who have fled quarantine centres in Zimbabwe and Malawi, as authorities worry they will spread COVID-19 in countries whose health systems can be overwhelmed rapidly.

item.title: NSW’s only drive-in cinema reopens
item.description: NSW's last remaining drive-in cinema has reopened offering entertainment goers a night out at the movies while adhering to social distancing practices.

item.title: China, US should respect key interests: Li
item.description: Chinese Premier Li Keqiang says Beijing and the United States should respect each other's core interests and manage their differences, adding that a decoupling of their economies is not good for the world.

item.title: Waivers on Iran nuke sites, US criticised
item.description: Russian senator Vladimir Dzhabarov says the United States' decision to end sanctions waivers, which had allowed some work to proceed at Iranian nuclear sites, will only provoke Tehran into developing nuclear weapons.

item.title: Qld woman dies in three-car collision
item.description: A woman has died after her car collided with two other vehicles in Queensland's Rockhampton region.

item.title: Pakistani plane crash voice recorder found
item.description: Search teams have recovered the cockpit voice recorder from the wreckage of last week's Pakistani airline crash.

item.title: Nissan to shut Indonesia, Spain car plants
item.description: Nissan has announced it will close auto plants in Spain and Indonesia, as it sinks into the red for the first time in 11 years, as the coronavirus pandemic sends global demand plunging and halts production.

item.title: Indonesia reports 23 deaths, 687 new cases
item.description: Indonesia has confirmed 23 new deaths and 687 additional coronavirus cases, bringing the total number of infections in the country to 24,538.
